LGTM - thanks for the patch @Hiebl. During the merge, I only did some minor code cleanups (avoid materialization of bin positions for quantiles), and left a FIXME for us to handle NaNs correctly (currently NaNs in the input would introduce zeros into the quantile computation).

@phaniarnab could you please address the NaN handling while finalizing your inputs to binning.
@OlgaOvcharenko once the federated quantile is ready, could you please extend the federated transform for equi-height as well?

Thanks everybody - this is a great addition.
